5/03/live-journey-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/journey">旅途</a>突然在电气火之后中途停止了一次休斯顿音乐会。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/journey-were-terrified-of-dont-stop-believin-being-used-in-teenybopper-show-glee-3781346">“不要停止相信”在“ teenybopper表演”&#39;Glee&#39;中被“害怕”。</a></strong></li></ul><p> The veteran rock band had performed just five songs when, midway through their mammoth 1981 hit &#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/journeys-dont-stop-believing-has-been-named-the-as-the-biggest-song-of-all-time-3608270">Don&#39;t Stop Believin</a> &#39;&#39;, they were forced to vacate the stage at NRG Stadium during the Houston Livestock Show and Rodeo on Friday (March 14).</p><p> A concert-goer later shared a video to X/Twitter, in which lead singer Arnel Pineda – who joined the band in 2007 – is seen singing the second verse of the song before the sound cuts out and the projector screens go dark.</p><p>观众显然感到困惑，但无论如何继续唱歌。 Members of Journey&#39;s crew later rushed to the stage with fire extinguishers, and per <a href="https://www.billboard.com/music/music-news/journey-cancels-houston-concert-electrical-fire-1235923016/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Billboard</em></a> , the crowd was informed that the concert would not continue and that everyone needed to evacuate.</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">哇。 <a href="https://twitter.com/JourneyOfficial?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@JourneyOfficial</a> show canceled at <a href="https://twitter.com/RODEOHOUSTON?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@RODEOHOUSTON</a> after electrical fire….in the middle of &#39;Don&#39;t Stop Believing.&#39; Here is when stage power went out. <a href="https://t.co/j0XWX0WHMV">pic.twitter.com/j0xwx0whmv</a></p><p> - 兰迪·克莱因（@rklein1010） <a href="https://twitter.com/rklein1010/status/1900745879490843106?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2025年3月15日</a></p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p>没有受伤。</p><p> Journey have not addressed the situation on social media, but the Houston Rodeo later issued an official statement about the cancellation on its Facebook page.</p><p> “Due to an unforeseen electrical incident under the stage area, we regretfully announce the cancellation of tonight&#39;s Journey concert. We sincerely apologize to all fans for this disappointment,” the organization wrote. “Our team is working diligently to assess the situation, and we will provide updates regarding rescheduling options and refunds as soon as possible.”</p><p> Fans seemed in good spirits about the incident, with one <a href="https://x.com/GallantSays/status/1900741447449493649" target="_blank" rel="noopener">joking</a> on X/Twitter: “Watched Journey in a smoky room, the sound died in the middle of THAT tune.” Meanwhile, others expressed frustration with the venue, with one writing they had “never seen this in all my years” of attending it.</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> Journey concert tonight <a href="https://twitter.com/RODEOHOUSTON?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@rodeohouston</a> abruptly ends due to a &quot;power outage&quot; on the stage. Band is escorted off and away from view. <a href="https://t.co/LMsgyMSF5e">pic.twitter.com/LMsgyMSF5e</a></p><p> — Gerald Cowen (@ByGeraldCowen) <a href="https://twitter.com/ByGeraldCowen/status/1900741035866628106?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">March 15, 2025</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p> Elsewhere, last year <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/journey-jonathan-cain-lawsuit-against-bandmate-neal-schon-3780870">the band&#39;s keyboardist Cain filed a lawsuit against guitarist Schon</a> while the band were on a co-headline tour in the US with <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/def-leppard">Def Leppard</a> , along with guests The Steve Miller Band and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/cheap-trick">Cheap Trick</a> . The suit was filed on grounds of frustrations over Schon&#39;s “expenses related to the tour” including “budgeting and spending” of the band&#39;s credit card over personal expenses.</p><p> Schon later revealed that the band <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/journey-bring-in-outside-party-to-help-resolve-jonathan-cain-neal-schon-dispute-3786584">opted to bring in “someone impartial” to help smooth over their differences</a> .</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/journey-abruptly-halt-houston-concert-during-dont-stop-believin-after-electrical-fire-3846636">Journey abruptly halt Houston concert during &#39;Don&#39;t Stop Believin” after electrical fire</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
 At least 51 people killed in North Macedonia nightclub fire, officials say https://www.nme.com/news/music/at-least-51-people-killed-in-north-macedonia-nightclub-fire-officials-say-3846617?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=at-least-51-people-killed-in-north-macedonia-nightclub-fire-officials-sayLaura Molloy Sun, 16 Mar 2025 10:31:20 +0000 Music NewsNews https://www.nme.com/?p=3846617 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/NME-news-breaking-1.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="NME新闻" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/NME-news-breaking-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/NME-news-breaking-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/NME-news-breaking-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/NME-news-breaking-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/NME-news-breaking-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/NME-news-breaking-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> Interior Minister Pance Toskovski has said that the blaze was probably caused by pyrotechnic devices “used for light effect at the concert”</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/at-least-51-people-killed-in-north-macedonia-nightclub-fire-officials-say-3846617">At least 51 people killed in North Macedonia nightclub fire, officials say</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/NME-news-breaking-1.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="NME新闻" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/NME-news-breaking-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/NME-news-breaking-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/NME-news-breaking-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/NME-news-breaking-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/NME-news-breaking-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/NME-news-breaking-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> At least 51 people have been killed and more than 100 have been injured in a fire at a nightclub in North Macedonia, officials say.</p><p> A fire was said to have broken out at 3am local time this morning (March 16) at the Pulse club in Kocani, a small town with around 30,000 inhabitants, around 100km (60 miles) east of the capital city Skopje.</p><p> Around 1500 people were in attendance for a concert by the hip-hop duo DNK, according to reports from the state news agency <a href="https://mia.mk/en/story/police-detain-kochani-nightclub-owner-after-deadly-fire%C2%A0" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>MIA</em></a> .</p><p> <em>MIA</em> said “at least 50 people died in a discotheque in Kočani”, where “around 1,500 people attended a concert”.</p><p> The concert started at midnight on Saturday (March 15) and was largely attended by young people, per <em><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/mar/16/north-macedonia-nightclub-fire-kocani-pulse" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Guardian</a></em> .</p><p> Injured concert-goers were reportedly taken either to the local hospital in Kočani, which initially reported 90 admissions (per <a href="https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/articles/c70wdedp20wo" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>BBC News</em></a> ) or to Štip, about 20 miles south. Many are suffering severe burns and have since been transferred to hospitals in Skopje for further treatment.</p><p> Footage shared on social media appears to show the band playing on stage when two flares go off, causing sparks to catch on the ceiling before rapidly spreading. Other clips circulating show the building engulfed in flames. </p><div id="fb-root"></div><p><script async="1" defer="1" crossorigin="anonymous" src="https://connect.facebook.net/en_US/sdk.js#xfbml=1&amp;version=v22.0"></script></p><div class="fb-post" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/MickoskiHristijan/posts/pfbid02ysZg4mhEbkz3SrNM2bo3TzPneBLUEMnCsGCU1iVha7cPGjyohdmcqs6bzHQK6tTjl" data-width="696"><blockquote cite="https://graph.facebook.com/100044158072981/posts/1248601373288453/" class="fb-xfbml-parse-ignore"><p> Со длабока тага ја примив веста за страшната трагедија во Кочани. Ова е тежок и многу тажен ден за Македонија! Загубата…</p><p> Posted by <a href="https://www.facebook.com/MickoskiHristijan">Hristijan Mickoski</a> on <a href="https://graph.facebook.com/100044158072981/posts/1248601373288453/">Sunday, March 16, 2025</a></p></blockquote></div><p> Interior Minister Pance Toskovski have speculated that the fire was probably caused by the use of pyrotechnic devices “used for light effect at the concert”.</p><p>托斯科夫斯基（Toskovski）在科卡尼警察局（Kocani）警察局面前告诉记者，烟火导致火花撞到天花板上，他据称这是用高度易燃物质制成的，然后大火在俱乐部的其余部分蔓延。</p><p> “在激活所谓的洒水器的那一刻，火花抓住了易燃材料制成的天花板，此后在很短的时间内，大火散布在整个迪斯科舞厅中，从而造成了浓烟，”他被引用了浓烟。” He said some arrests had been made.</p><p> We have some more comments from interior minister Panche Toshkovski that are being carried by the Agence France-Presse (AFP) news agency.</p><p>总理赫里斯蒂安·米科斯基（Hristijan Mickoski）在<a href="https://www.facebook.com/MickoskiHristijan/posts/pfbid02ysZg4mhEbkz3SrNM2bo3TzPneBLUEMnCsGCU1iVha7cPGjyohdmcqs6bzHQK6tTjl?__cft__[0]=AZVjAlva5H5r2giWBqnFUZ0wgUoH_53gktNm3_fRGn4dZ37O_qKvnlSIpf9pkdzeMIEMY05CW1cV-WZmXWzyCfjsnxBbHeJRZY0UUUKVcmEml3XXE9sa4-mjYwY4Z1D8de2dzOD9WKfaFTUatV87zLzxbHT5_2691kGUL-BFZvvTAG88yFq3t3EjxBStKUxScFM&amp;__tn__=%2CO%2CP-R" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Facebook上的一份声明</a>中写道，政府“完全动员了，将尽一切必要来应对后果并确定这场悲剧的原因”</p><p> He called it a “difficult and very sad day” for the country, which has now lost “so many” young lives.</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/at-least-51-people-killed-in-north-macedonia-nightclub-fire-officials-say-3846617">At least 51 people killed in North Macedonia nightclub fire, officials say</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
